events.name: レストラン厨房外出ドア

parameters:
\N<Chef>Nuu... No, it's no good! Not at all! Another
failure...!

\N<Chef>Damn it! I'll start over! With this, I won't be
able to create the dish I desire!!

\N<Chef>I'll have to rethink this from scratch... If the
foundation is different, I won't be able to create
anything.

\N<Chef>Damn it, if only I had that ingredient, I could
definitely get closer to the taste I desire...

\N<Chef>Wait a minute... Maybe I can substitute this...?
Alright, let's try it with this next time...

\CE[84]\N<Rain>(This... I can definitely feel the incredible
dedication...)

\N<Rain>(I wonder if this is also because of the influence
of Nightmare Heaven...)
\CE[84]\N<Rain>Um, Chef. Can I talk to you for a moment?

\N<Chef>Ah!!? What is it!! I told you not to disturb me
while I'm cooking, didn't I?!
\N<Chef>Ahh!! Damn it, I messed up! This is no good...!!

\N<Chef>Look! It's another failure because of you! You
idiot!

\CE[84]\N<Rain>U-Um, excuse me. But, could you listen to me for a
moment?

\N<Chef>How many times do I have to say it! This
restaurant depends on my cooking! I don't have
time to talk about anything else!! If you're not a
chef, then shut up!!!

\N<Chef>At least bring me the ingredients I want before
coming!! If you understand, then disappear!

\CE[79]\N<Rain>(There's no other choice... I guess I'll have to
listen to what they say here.)

\CE[79]\N<Rain>Understood, I will procure the ingredients. Please
tell me what ingredients you want.

\N<Chef>What...? Are you going to get the ingredients for
me?

\N<Rain>Yes. In exchange, if I bring them properly, will
you listen to what I have to say?
\N<Chef>Ah, fine. If you bring them properly.

\N<Chef>The desired ingredients and where to obtain them
are written in this note! Hurry up and go!

You can now visit the Grassy Plains from the world
map.
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ指定 2

\EMP If I put it in at this timing... no, that's
not right... mumble mumble mumble...
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ強制終了 2

\N<Chef>Oh! This is it, this is it! I've been waiting for
this!

\N<Chef>Alright, let's start cooking right away! This time
it should go well!!
\N<Rain>Um, Chef. Please listen to what I have to say───

\CE[79]\CE[84]\N<Rain>(Hmm, this is troublesome... In the end, I won't
be able to have my story heard...)

\N<Rain>(But if the cooking goes well, maybe the problem
will be solved. For now, let's see how things
go...)

\CE[79]\N<Rain>──So, I would like to wait for the dish to be
completed.
\N<Waiter>Yes, I see... I'll pray for it to go well.

\N<Waiter>Thank you for handling the situation. If the dish
is ready, please come visit us. We will treat you
to a delicious meal.
'You have earned a reward of \x1bC[17]1000 Meta and +5\x1bC[0] Blessing Points.'
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ指定 2
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ強制終了 2
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ指定 1

\EMP Ugh! Chef has been so obsessed with
researching new dishes, and I'm the one who's
always busy...!
EMW_メッセージウィンドウ強制終了 1
